OL,6,F"Every victim needs to be recognised.
OL,7,FEveryone needs to be recognised. This
OL,8,Fshould never have happened."
OL,10,FNow though, six years after it was
OL,11,Flaunched, the public inquiry will end
OL,12,Fon Monday and while many have hope
OL,13,Fthey'll soon have answers, they say
OL,14,Fthey'll never have justice.
OL,16,FSue Sparks' husband, Les, was a
OL,17,Fhaemophiliac, but a fear of needles
OL,18,Fmade him reluctant to get treatment.
